					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-409760#post-4374760</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-409760/scp-1011#post-4374760</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 24 Sep 2019 20:16:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Nagiros</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4665703</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Upvote bordering on novote because although the anomaly is functionally an indictment of capitalism, the article is ambivalent about whether it wants to mock capitalism for its overt hostility to the working class or mock communism by co-opting it's rhetoric in a body horror SCP.</p> <p>A previous commentor requested the perspectives of family members, but I request the perspective of the anomaly itself. Is it an embodiment of communism, or is it the manifestation of the manager, the foreman, the petite bourgeoisie? Looking at the base facts of the narrative, it appears to be the latter, so why the ambiguity?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
